The article discusses the issue of loopholes in US immigration laws that have allowed criminals, including MS-13 gang members, to enter communities. It criticizes Democrats in Congress for refusing to close these loopholes, including the practice of catch and release. The article argues that recent illegal immigration data highlights the need to address the crisis at the border caused by these loopholes. It also accuses Congressional Democrats of creating loopholes that make it difficult to remove illegal aliens from Central America. The article further claims that Democrats have obstructed efforts to address the immigration crisis and have advocated for open borders.